The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Global learning solutions company Aptech Limited has posted a 39 per cent growth in income from operations at Rs 52.24 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 37.55 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The profit before ESOP compensation cost and tax was up 17 per cent at Rs 8.60 crore compared with Rs 7.32 crore in the corresponding quarter a year ago. Product launches, extensive marketing campaigns and introduction of fortified products have contributed to our impressive booking growth this quarter, said Pramod Khera, CEO amp; managing director of Aptech.

 Orchid Chemicals amp; Pharmaceuticals has reported a 253 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 51.30 crore for the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 14.59 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal. The total income was Rs 291.36 crore compared with Rs 202.49 crore the year-ago period. Gross profit before interest, depreciation and tax rose 96 per cent to Rs 115.38 crore from Rs 58.79 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.

 Electrosteel Castings Ltd has reported a revenue of Rs 320.83 crore for the first quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 260.61 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal. Profit after tax jumped 57 per cent to Rs 29.82 crore, while profit before tax increased 41 per cent to 41.72 crore.

 Shree Cement has posted a 13 per cent rise in turnover at Rs 426 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 378 crore for the quarter ended March 31, 2007. The operating profit increased to Rs 195 crore from Rs 160 crore in the quarter ended March 31. Cement sales volumes rose by 12 per cent.

 LG Electronics has launched 3D LCD monitor and two notebooks Z1 and S900. Z1 is Indias first notebook with auxiliary display. S900 blends the power of desktop PCs with the convenience of notebooks. 

 Tata Indicom has launched Sungil USB modem Plug2SurfWHIZ. The gadget is a wireless device that directly fits into a standard USB port. 

 Parryware has laun-ched The Tiger brand of taps that have a 10-year warranty and water saving foam flow aerators.

 Pepe Jeans London has started an end-of-season sale in the city. There is a discount of up to 50 per cent on all goods.

 The marketing director of Centurion Bank of Punjab is Yateesh Srivastava and not Yateesh Gupta as appeared in The Telegraph on July 23, 2007.

